{
  "name": "Expert Commander",
  "type": "feature",
  "img": "icons/environment/people/charge.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p>You gain the following benefits for your Commander Class Features.</p><p></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Commander's Call</span></strong></span></p><p>The range of your Commander’s Call increases to 10 Spaces.</p><p>When you use Commander’s Call, you can spend 2 additional SP to issue the creature 1 additional command of your choice. The creature chooses the order in which it resolves the granted commands.</p><p><em><strong>Example:</strong> You use Commander’s Call on an ally and spend 2 additional SP, 3 SP total. You choose the Move and Attack Commands. The creature chooses to up to their Speed without provoking Opportunity Attacks first and then Attacks with ADV after moving.</em></p><p><em><strong>DC Tip:</strong> You can still only use each command once on each of your turns.</em></p><p></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Inspiring Presence</span></strong></span></p><p>The amount of HP restored by Inspiring Presence is increased by 1.</p><p></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Commanding Aura</span></strong></span></p><p>When you help a creature within your Commanding Aura, your Help Die starts at a d10.</p><p>When you use Commanding Aura, you can spend additional SP to enhance its effect:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Rally:</strong> The Temp HP granted increases by 1 per 2 SP spent.</p></li><li><p><strong>Reinforce:</strong> You can spend 1 SP to grant the target ADV on any Saves made as part of the Attack.</p></li></ul>",
